The paper deals with the analysis of a benchmark task for recurrent neural networks, specifically the NARMA10 task. This task is widely used in the field of reservoir computing, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also analyzes the properties of the NARMA10 model from a dynamical system perspective, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to the category of dynamical systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper evaluates the information processing capacity of the model, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new benchmark model that is more stable and robust, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
